{{zh-hanzi|[[古]][[琴]]}}
'''古琴''' is a Chinese word meaning "ancient zither", more specifically, the [[guqin]].
{{wikipediapar|Guqin}}
==Chinese==
[[Image:Lian Zhu Shi.jpg|thumb|right|150px|An antique ''guqin'' in the ''lianzhu'' form]]
===Etymology===
From [[古]] ‘ancient’ + [[琴]] ‘stringed instrument’

===Pronunciation===
*[[Mandarin]]: {{Audio|zh-gu3qin2.ogg|gǔqín}}
*{{IPA|[kutɕʰin]}}
*Plain: "goo-chin"

'''Romanizations'''
